# BlackHoleResearch — project context

This is **scientific software** for multiwavelength black-hole astrophysics.
The bar is higher than a typical app: numbers are honest, formulas are cited,
plots are reproducible from on-screen metadata.

## Required reading (in priority order)

1. `AGENTS.md` — operational rules for all contributors.
2. `PHASE2_PLAN.md` — milestone roadmap. Exit criteria are binary.
3. `docs/PITFALLS.md` — normative failure-mode catalog.

## Prime directives (memorize)

1. **Honesty over completeness** — never invent a value. Return `None` /
   `upper_limit=True` / `UncalibratedDataError` instead of a fake number.
2. **Cite every formula** — primary-source reference in every physics
   function docstring.
3. **astropy.units end-to-end** — bare floats for physical quantities are
   a bug.
4. **Tests precede expansion** — no PR merges without a regression test.
5. **Streamlit is presentation only** — physics and I/O live in
   `blackhole/`; `app.py` may only render.
6. **Single source of truth** — sources in `blackhole/catalog.py`,
   calibrations in `blackhole/calibration.py`, constants from
   `astropy.constants`.
7. **Provenance with every plot** — file SHA, calibration version,
   function chain.

## Quick-reference map

| Need | Path |
|---|---|
| Add a source | `blackhole/catalog.py` |
| Add a survey calibrator | `blackhole/calibration.py` |
| New physics formula | `blackhole/physics/<topic>.py` |
| FITS I/O | `blackhole/io.py` |
| UI rendering | `app.py` (presentation only) |
| Architectural decision | `docs/adr/ADR-NNNN-title.md` |
| New failure mode | append to `docs/PITFALLS.md` |
